In this article, President Trump is asked about his reaction to the terror attacks in London. He describes it as a terrible thing that continues to happen. He emphasizes the need for being smart and tough in dealing with such attacks. He mentions that he will be calling the Prime Minister of the United Kingdom. When asked if he has been briefed on the London bomb attack, he confirms that he has been briefed on numerous things, including North Korea. He expresses the intention to get a briefing and meet with someone named Frank. He reiterates the importance of being tougher and smarter in addressing these issues.